n-bottom:0px;">Thomas Saunders, who died in 2022, was a managing director a=
nd chairman at
Morgan Stanley for two decades=E2=80=94where he structured I.P.O.s for comp=
anies like Apple and GE, and did the underwriting for <strong>Margaret That=
cher</strong>=E2=80=99s telecom privatization=E2=80=94before going on to co=
-found his own private equity firm. He also served as chairman of the Herit=
age Foundation, which of course famously authored Project 2025. The couple =
were active philanthropists, with much of their largesse going to Virginia =
institutions such as UVA, the Virginia Military Institute, and the Thomas
Jefferson Foundation.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Jordan first tested the auction w=
aters by offering English and European furniture, silver, ceramics, and Chi=
nese export porcelain in a single-owner sale at Sotheby=E2=80=99s in Februa=
ry 2024, including items she=E2=80=99d purchased in the Duke and Duchess of=
 Windsor sale there in 1998. The sale of 316 objects made $3.3 million, aga=
inst an estimate of $2 million.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:
0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Additional highlig=
hts in the upcoming sale include a de Heem large-scale floral still life at=
 an estimate of $8 million, higher than the artist=E2=80=99s current auctio=
n record of $7.6 million. Mel=C3=A9ndez=E2=80=99s <em>Still Life with a Cau=
liflower </em>is estimated at $5 million, and Lawrence=E2=80=99s <em>Portra=
it of Miss Julia Peel</em> is estimated at $6 million. It is the best examp=
le by the artist to appear at auction in nearly two decades, when the aucti=
on
record of $4 million was set. A rare pair of Hals portraits is on offer for=
 $6 million, and a genre scene by Dou, a student of <strong>Rembrandt</stro=
ng>, is estimated at $5 million. Thomas recalled seeing the Dou painting on=
 view in a 2001 traveling exhibition of the artist=E2=80=99s works: =E2=80=
=9CWhat can I say about my feelings as I looked at our Dou hanging in the N=
ational Gallery in Washington next to <strong>Queen Elizabeth II</strong>=
=E2=80=99s Dou? God bless America!=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">After London, the paintings are touring to=
 Amsterdam and Brussels during TEFAF Maastricht, then Los Angeles and Hong =
Kong in April. As Jordan would tell the next generation of collectors, =E2=
=80=9CLong live the hunt!=E2=80=9D</p></div>
